Thank you for this great tutorial!
 If someone wants to limit paddles movement in y direction you can do this:

def paddle_a_up():
    y = paddle_a.ycor()
    if y < 250:
        y += 20
        paddle_a.sety(y)

def paddle_a_down():
    y = paddle_a.ycor()
    if y > -250:
        y -= 20
        paddle_a.sety(y)

A cool little thing you can add to the code as well is a direction randomizer every time the ball is in the center by importing "random" and then adding something like this:

if ball.xcor() == 0 and ball.ycor() == 0:
        firstDirection = random.randint(0,3)
        if firstDirection == 1:
            ball.dx *= -1
            ball.dy *= 1
        elif firstDirection == 2:
            ball.dx *= 1
            ball.dy *= -1
        elif firstDirection == 3:
            ball.dx *= -1
            ball.dy *= -1

